# Go Package Aliases

Default to the package's declared name in Go imports. Do not add an alias just
to make the import "more descriptive".

## Rules

- Prefer `import "path/to/pkg"` over `alias "path/to/pkg"` when the package name is already clear.
- Only add an alias when it is actually needed:
  - the file imports two packages with the same package name
  - the default package name is misleading or too ambiguous in that file
  - the alias follows an established repository convention that improves consistency
- Do not invent aliases like `servermetrics`, `mongostore`, or similar if `metrics` / `mongo` already read clearly.
- Existing repo-wide conventions such as `pb` for generated protobuf packages, and other widely established short aliases already used throughout the codebase, may be kept for consistency.

## Examples

```go
// Bad
import servermetrics "github.com/superdurable/dex/server/internal/metrics"
import mongostore "github.com/superdurable/dex/server/internal/persistence/mongo"

// Good
import "github.com/superdurable/dex/server/internal/metrics"
import "github.com/superdurable/dex/server/internal/persistence/mongo"
```
